{
    "analysis": "From the previous execution we have loaded metric, trace, log, and error_logs data and computed global summary stats (including per-group P95) for each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) across the full series. The top suspects from that global summary are ts-travel-service (high disk I/O, high memory, many sockets, elevated latency). We must now perform windowed anomaly detection using the precomputed global thresholds (P95) but only inspect the incident window. Per the rules, thresholds must be from the full series (already computed). The next step is to detect anomalies inside the incident window for only the allowed root-cause candidate services (ts-auth-service, ts-order-service, ts-route-service, ts-train-service, ts-travel-service) and produce a compact aggregate of anomaly counts and earliest anomaly timestamps so we can narrow down faulty component-KPIs.",
